 CONCEPTION OF THE UNIVERSAL AVAILABILITY OF PUBLICATIONS PROGRAMME AND ITSPRACTICAL RESULTS.     BRIEFLY DESCRIBES THE MOST IMPORTANT PHASES OF THE UNIVERSAL AVAILABILITY OFPUBLICATIONS (UAP) PROGRAMME. ANALYSES THE CONNECTION BETWEEN THE PROGRAMMEAND INTER-LIBRARY LENDING. OUTLINES THE CONCEPTUAL PROBLEMS OF A NATIONALINTER-LIBRARY LENDING SYSTEM MODEL AND PRESENTS 4 BASIC MODELS SPECIFYINGTHEIR ADVANTAGES AND DISADVANTAGES. FINALLY DESCRIBES SOME PRACTICAL RESULTSOF THE UAP PROGRAMME IN RELATION TO BRAZIL, BULGARIA, FRANCE, EAST GERMANY,MALAYSIA, NORWAY, UK AND USA